Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light purplish brown; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 46. Probably a better preserved example from the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0696.10. Name Menon.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0609)
